OL,3,CSunderland condemn online racist abuse
OL,4,Cof Brian Brobbey after Tottenham game
OL,6,FSunderland AFC have condemned racist
OL,7,Fabuse directed towards Brian Brobbey
OL,8,Fon social media, and offered the
OL,9,Fstriker their full support.
OL,11,FThe club said the 24-year-old was
OL,12,Ftargeted online after the Black Cats'
OL,13,F1-0 win over Tottenham in the Premier
OL,14,FLeague on Sunday (12 April).
OL,16,FA club statement said: "Sunderland
OL,17,Fcondemns in the strongest possible
OL,18,Fterms the racist abuse directed at
OL,19,FBrian Brobbey on social media.
OL,26,@xD@XOU
