OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F429A1776255072
OL,3,CSunderland condemn online racist abuse
OL,4,Cof Brian Brobbey after Tottenham game
OL,6,F"We stand firmly with Brian and offer
OL,7,Fhim our full and unwavering support."
OL,9,FIt is not the first time Sunderland
OL,10,Fplayers have been targeted by racist
OL,11,Fabuse this season.
OL,13,FRomaine Mundle was sent online abuse
OL,14,Ffollowing February's game against
OL,15,FFulham, while last month's Tyne-Wear
OL,16,Fderby was paused following a report of
OL,17,Fabuse from the crowd aimed at
OL,18,FLutsharel Geertruida.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@eO]
